      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ICE CANDY (5) is super consistent without winning, landing six placings from eight starts. Was below best last time when missed the frame finishing fifth (23.40) at Ballarat. Solid formlines coming through her last run. Has ability and is a key runner. TRIPLE THREAT (8) held his own to the line last start and filled a minor placing, beaten only 1.3 lengths (26.07) behind Kraken Sandy at Shepparton. Form from his last run is proving strong. Well placed and gets his chance. MISS DUDDLES (1) is still a maiden after 11 runs but rarely out of the placings, the latest filling a minor again when second at Warragul. The form from her last run stacks up well. Expected to be in the finish again. TALTARNI SUZY (2) is building a nice sequence of placings – hard to fault that form.",
